OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBilsdale transmitter:      
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FArqiva apologises for fire 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fdamage signal delays       
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The boss of the firm which owns the    
OL,6, fire-damaged Bilsdale TV mast has said 
OL,7, sorry for delays in restoring services.
OL,9,FThe 1,032ft (315m) tall mast caught    
OL,10,Ffire on 10 August and affected TV and  
OL,11,Fradio for a million people across North
OL,12,FYorkshire, Teesside and County Durham. 
OL,14,FArqiva chief executive Paul Donovan    
OL,15,Fapologised but said replacing the      
OL,16,F500-tonne transmitter "at the flick of 
OL,17,Fa switch" was not feasible.            
OL,19,FHe said a probe into the fire continued
OL,20,Fbut ruled out vandalism or arson.      
